1.2 Option switch setting in antenna rule
    a.Please set the correct total metal counts in your design.DRC default to check 10 level metal.
      For 10 level metal, please set this option to “M 10”;
      For 9 level metal, please set this option to “M 9”;
      For 8 level metal, please set this option to “M 8”;
      For 7 level metal, please set this option to “M 7”;
      For 6 level metal, please set this option to “M 6”;
      For 5 level metal, please set this option to “M 5”;
      For 4 level metal, please set this option to “M 4”;

    b.Please set the correct top metal counts in your design.DRC default to check 2 top metal.
      For one top metal count,please set this option to “T 1”.

    c.Please set the correct top metal in your design.DRC default to check normal top metal,
      For ultra thickness top metal, please set this option to “TM_NAME TM2”.

    d.Please set the correct ALPA thickness in your design.DRC default to check 1.45um thickness ALPA,
      For 2.8um thickness ALPA,please set this option “2.8”.



2. Calibre version requirement: 2016.3_19.12
This drc runset is verified by 2016.3_19.12 version Calibre,so advise
user also use 2016.3_19.12 version Calibre to do drc check for your design.



3. Known issues
MTT2_13 may have false alarm in below pattern:
Two TV2 are located on the same TM1 and on the same MTT2, but they are located on the different intersect region of TM1 and MTT2. 
If the space between the two TV2 is <= 1.7um,it is also a good pattern,but DRC would highlight it.

